Review: middle class morality can kiss my arse

This to me was less about mona and more about the individuals she encountered along the way; everyone seemed to fit neatly within the bounds of a distinct archetype (e.g. professor, rural worker, mechanic). mona’s inability to (& oftentimes refusal to) commit to any of these societally acceptable roles in her pursuit of an illusive idea of freedom brings about her tragedy; “freedom” (or a semblance of it) in a late-capitalist world is only really attainable by adhering to an…
best thing I’ve watched in a very long time
